The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, December 22, 2002 				 Driver killed in tanker hijack
																								Siliguri, Dec. 21: An oil-tanker driver was shot dead and his helper seriously injured when alleged Bihar-based criminals hijacked the vehicle from Panitanki, near the Indo-Nepal border, in the wee hours today, reports our correspondent.																								Uttam Roy was rushed to North Bengal Medical College and Hospital, where his condition was stated to be extremely critical. Following a tip-off, Bihar police traced three members of the gang in Araria district.
